    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nIf `$VIMRUNTIME` is inaccessible, using a builtin Lua module fails with its usual error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nE5108: Error executing lua vim/_init_packages.lua:0: module 'vim.version' not found:\r\n\tno field package.preload['vim.version']\r\n\tno file '/Users/runner/work/neovim/neovim/.deps/usr/share/luajit-2.1/vim/version.lua'\r\n        ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut none of the listed paths mention the `$VIMRUNTIME` directory. This can be confusing for new users (especially for embedded Nvim): https://github.com/vscode-neovim/vscode-neovim/issues/1815\r\n\r\nNote that _by default_, macOS applications such as VSCode don't have access to `~/Downloads`. So if an application embeds Nvim, it can _run_ `nvim` but the runtime won't work. This is confusing because it _will_ work in your terminal (if your terminal has access to `~/Downloads`).\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nSteps vary per OS. Steps for macOS:\r\n\r\n1. download the [latest Nvim](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases) to `~/Downloads`.\r\n1. ensure your terminal app does _not_ have access permissions to `Downloads`:\r\n    - <img width=\"457\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/vscode-neovim/vscode-neovim/assets/1359421/a9f13422-27ad-4129-90f3-6792407f0083\">\r\n1. in your terminal, run `nvim` from the Downloads folder.\r\n   ```\r\n   ~/Downloads/nvim-macos/bin/nvim\r\n   ```\r\n1. Try to use a non-builtin Lua runtime file:\r\n   ```\r\n   :lua =vim.version\r\n   ```\r\n1. Try `!ls $VIMRUNTIME`:\r\n   ```\r\n   :!ls $VIMRUNTIME\r\n   ls: /Users/xx/Downloads/t/nvim-macos/share/nvim/runtime: Operation not permitted\r\n   shell returned 1\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n\r\n## Expected behavior\r\n\r\n- If `$VIMRUNTIME` is set to an unreadable directory, show an explicit error on startup.\r\n    - We already _accidentally_ show `E484: Can't open file x/syntax/syntax.vim`, but that doesn't make it obvious that the problem is a permissions issue with `$VIMRUNTIME`.\r\n- Lua loader error should say if it can't access `$VIMRUNTIME`, or include it in the \"failed to access paths\" list?\r\n\r\n",
